summary: A ENB compilation of four different presets branded "The Mistveil" to provide the player unique and fascinating atmospheres in Skyrim, based on the seasons: Winter, Spring, Summer and Autumn.
descriptionHtml:
[center][img]http://i.imgur.com/EdaBGCs.png[/img][/center]
[center]The Mistveil ENBs born from a simple concept: to give the players a specific atmosphere for their Skyrim, based on the 4 seasons: Winter, Spring, Summer and Autumn.
Every preset has its own personality, focus and obviously its own setting files.
The four presets are meant to use almost all ENB's features, so they could be quite demanding in terms of performance.
However you are free to ask tips and advice to increase the performances, but keep in mind [i]"asking is lawful, answering is courtesy"[/i][/center]

[center]The Mistveil presets offer the player many features adopted in other wonderful settings like [url=http://skyrim.nexusmods.com/mods/38944//?]K ENB[/url] and [url=http://skyrim.nexusmods.com/mods/24235/]Phinix ENB[/url]
[font=italic]SMAA SubPixel Morphological Anti Aliasing, SweetFX integrated
Boulotaur's SweetFX Version, credits to CeeJay.dk and Boulotaur
Chained HQ PostSharpen Plugin via InjFX Shaders
Custom Bloom by Kyokushinoyama
Kinematic Sharpening by Kyokushinoyama and Zeroking
Extensive Sunsprite Shaders and Textures by --Jawz--
Anamorphic Lenz Flare, credits to Matso
Customizable Dynamic DOF, by Kyokushinoyama
SweetFX shaders, courtesy of CeeJay.dk and Boulotaur
Enbeffect.fx codes by Kyokushinoyama, HeliosDoubleSix (HD6), ZeroKing and --Jawz--
Color Correction integrated in the ENB GUI, by --Jawz--
Eye Adaptation Code and HD6's color correction code GUI integration with interior/exterior separation, courtesy of Phinix[/font][/center]
[center][img]http://i.imgur.com/JUZNpjr.png[/img][/center]
[center][img]http://i.imgur.com/aFPXXst.png[/img][/center]
[center][img]http://i.imgur.com/GPhXQRo.png[/img][/center]
[center]First of all you need the supported binaries (wrapper version only) on [url=http://www.enbdev.com/index_en.htm]ENBDev[/url], but you can use the binaries starting from the .217/.221, downloadable from [url=http://beautifulskyrim.yolasite.com/enb-binaries.php]Beautiful Skyrim[/url].
[size=+2]Very Important![/size]
1)Clean your Skyrim folder from every ENB file you were using before, especially [b]injector.ini[/b] because it is not needed and causes graphic issues.
I also suggest you to delete the folder named [b]enbseries[/b] because certain presets' files can conflict with The Mistveil ENB, since it uses its own.
2)Go to MyDocuments/MyGames/Skyrim and edit Skyrimprefs.ini as it follows:[/center]

[center]bFloatPointRenderTarget=1[/center]
[center]bTreesReceiveShadows=1[/center]
[center]bDrawLandShadows=1[/center]
[center]bShadowsOnGrass=1[/center]

[center]Now we can proceed to the Installation process:[/center]
[list][*] Download one of the four presets[*] Extract all the files in Skyrim's [b]MAIN[/b] folder[*] [b]VERY IMPORTANT[/b] open enblocal.ini and find the line VideoMemorySizeMb=3072, you have to manually put your VRAM value by using one of the following formulas (credit to [url=http://skyrim.nexusmods.com/users/2327456]Zeroking[/url]):VRAM + RAM - 2048 -or- VRAM + (RAM/2) - 2048 -or- VRAM[*] Play[/list]
[center]For more info [url=http://skyrim.nexusmods.com/mods/39742//?]Jawz ENB Guide

[/url]If you wanna update to binary .250/.260: download the archive under "UPDATES" and
follow the instruction written above.

[b][size=+2]Latest binaries supported: [color=red].250 [/color]and[color=red] .260[/size][/color][/b]
To use the latest ENB's feature you need a water mod compatible, at the moment I know of:
[url=http://skyrim.nexusmods.com/mods/13268//?]WATER - Water And Terrain Enhancement Redux[/url]
[url=http://skyrim.nexusmods.com/mods/1111//?]Pure Waters[/url][/center]
[center]Before installing a new enb preset I suggest you to do a clean [b]uninstallation[/b] of the previous ENB preset:[/center]
[list][*] remove all the enb files and folders inside Skyrim's main folder,[*] delete Rendererinfo.txt and the 2 ini files ([size=+2]Backup them first![/size]), [*] start the game from the Launcher and choose your video settings,[*] close the game, put your backup inis back in MyDocuments/Games/Skyrim[*] Play with the new preset[/list]
[center][size=+2]Still doubts about how to install the ENB? Check this video by Hodilton:[/size]
[youtube]rJbtB6A3sdo[/youtube][/center]

[center]- Is it compatible with CoT or other weather mods?
I don't use them and I haven't tweaked these preset on those mods, so I suggest you to NOT use them.
If you do and the presets have issues or they don't look as they would, it's on you.

- Is it compatible with Lightning Overhaul mods?
The only one is ELFX and ONLY the esps for interiors, like I wrote above.
You are free to try them, but I can't guarantee the result and I'll not take responsability for it.

- I have a big performance drop, what can I do?
First of all, check the enblocal.ini's VideoMemorySize, have you followed the formulas I wrote? Have you tried all three of them?
Consider that The Mistveil can be demanding on AMD graphic card, but usually what hits more the performance are these values in enbseries.ini:
EnableSkyLighting=true
EnableReflection=true
EnableDepthOfField=true
EnableAmbientOcclusion=true
You can try set them to "false" starting from the first one, you'll probably lose some visual quality but you'll gain some FPS.
Another way to improve performance is disabling injFX.h by editing this line in SweetFX_settings.txt:
external_d3d9_wrapper = d3d9_Sharpen.dll -> change to "none"
This will also speed up the loading screens, at cost of color precision and sharpening.
Don't expect miracles, though.

- The nights are too dark!
Use torches, magelight, candlelight.. the nights in these presets are supposed to be dark, yes.
And I will not change them.

- The shadows are too dark!
This is something I concede to change, go in enbseries.ini and find these lines:
[SKYLIGHTING]
AmbientMinLevelSunrise
AmbientMinLevelDay
AmbientMinLevelSunset
AmbientMinLevelNight
AmbientMinLevelInteriorDay
AmbientMinLevelInteriorNight
The higher the values, the brighter the shadows. But WATCH OUT! It will change ALL the shadows in that specific daytime! Nights aren't affected!

- What mod are you using in the picture xxx ?
I put the author name in the picture, you have the links of their profile below, ask them directly. That's the best I can do to help you about this ^^'

- Are you the same Modd3r from Differently Ebony and Glass Variants? When Cabal120 will release *randomtexture* ?
Ehm.. yes I am, but this isn't very related to The Mistveil ENB, isn't it?[/center]
